## Which Pear Settings Work Best with a Black Diamond Center

Black diamonds interact with settings entirely through surface reflection, not light transmission. Setting choice is a contrast decision: how much brightness surrounds the black stone to make the opacity read as dramatic rather than merely dark.

### Halo Settings: Maximum Contrast

A halo of white diamonds surrounding a black pear creates the strongest visual contrast available in any ring design — jet-black stone against a circle of white brilliance. This is the correct setting framework for any buyer who wants the black pear's opacity to read as intentional and architectural rather than subdued.

