The [Twisted Halo](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/twisted-halo-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-item-sku-192890?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) at [$1,955 (197 reviews)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/twisted-halo-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-item-sku-192890?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the most-reviewed pear setting in this catalog and the strongest recommendation for a black pear center. The twisted frame creates dynamic light return that rotates as the hand moves — paired with a static, non-refracting black center, this kinetic contrast is more visually interesting than a static flat halo. For all halo options, see the **[pear diamond halo ring guide](/pear-diamond-halo-ring)**.

The [Graduated Diamond Halo](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/graduated-diamond-halo-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-305177?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) at [$2,985 (99 reviews)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/graduated-diamond-halo-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-305177?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) provides denser, more formal coverage around the pear outline — graduating diamonds follow the teardrop taper and create maximum pear-perimeter brightness. For large black pears (3ct+) where the stone has significant physical presence, the Graduated Halo provides proportional setting coverage.

### Pavé Settings: Best for Clean Contrast

Pavé settings pair a bright, continuous white diamond shank with the black pear center, directing the eye to the stone through brightness gradient rather than encirclement. White gold pavé in white gold is the most dramatic contrast presentation.

