**What is a pear shaped black diamond engagement ring?** A pear shaped black diamond engagement ring features a GIA or IGI certified Fancy Black pear-cut diamond — fully opaque, jet-black, available from 1.01ct to 9.69ct on Blue Nile from $1,368. All stones carry CO clarity, which is universal and optically irrelevant for opaque black diamonds.

**Key buying frameworks:** (1) The Opacity Advantage — black diamonds are fully opaque, eliminating bow-tie, making CO clarity irrelevant, giving all stones identical Fancy Black grade, and making carat weight the only purchase variable. (2) The Carat-Per-Dollar Inversion — per-carat price falls as carat weight increases; a 4.70ct black pear at $1,118/ct costs less per carat than a 1.01ct at $1,561/ct. Buy the largest stone your budget allows.

**Best settings by aesthetic:** Maximum contrast → Twisted Halo WG ($1,955 / 197 reviews) or Graduated Diamond Halo JA WG ($2,985 / 99 reviews). Gothic romantic yellow gold → Hand-Engraved Micropavé YG ($1,600 / 87 reviews) or Enchanted Scroll YG ($1,670 / 37 reviews). Clean modern → Scalloped Pavé WG ($1,970 / 164 reviews).

**Complete ring budgets:** GIA 1.17ct + Twisted Halo WG = ~$3,323. GIA 2.01ct + Scalloped Pavé WG = ~$4,979. GIA 4.70ct + Twisted Halo WG = ~$7,210. GIA 7.45ct + Graduated Halo JA WG = ~$9,700.

